locations.name: Bivouac Hut (Staircase Spur) HLS
locations.adviceToPilots:
- Elevation 5820ft - high elevation site so potential for high winds and snow/ice in winter.
- National Park.
- Suitable for DAY use. No lighting installed.
- NO prior notification required.
- Restrictions on use = NIL.
- Approach and departure CLEAR of vertical structures. 
- No houses / buildings under flight.
- No powerlines present.
- No adjacent trees.
- Site is on top of a knoll, slight downward slope off the edge of the knoll.
- Site surface is grassy vegetation and natural rock.
- No support vehicle access.
- One helicopter only (at a time).
- If fuel or oil spill, damage to alpine vegetation may occur.
- Nil stock, wildlife or waterfowl likely to be present.
- Members of public - potentially present due to walking track nearby. Management of public may be required during holiday periods (small numbers of hikers only).

locations.name: Cleve Cole Hut (Mount Bogong) HLS
locations.adviceToPilots:
- Elevation 5890ft. Adverse weather possible due to elevation - potential for high winds, and snow/ice in winter.
- Suitable for DAY use.
- NO prior notification required.
- Approach and departure clear of vertical structures.
- No houses/buildings under flight.
- No powerlines.
- Trees adjacent to landing area are snow gums up to 10m high, clear from site by at least 20m.
- Undulating slope in the area as site sits on a knoll.
- Low grassy vegetation and natural rock.
- Nil support vehicle access, not accessible by road.
- One helicopter only.
- If fuel or oil spill, damage to alpine vegetation may occur.
- No stock, wildlife or waterfowl likely to be present.
- Members of public possible as the site is adjacent to walking tracks. Management of public may be required during holiday periods (small number of hikers only).
- No lighting.

locations.name: Michell Hut Site (Eskdale Spur, Granite Flat Spur) HLS
locations.adviceToPilots:
- Elevation 5715ft - therefore potential for high winds. Snow covered in winter (potentially icy). 
- Snow poles and undulating slopes in landing site area.
- Suitable for DAY use .
- No prior notification required.
- No restrictions on use.
- Approach and departure paths are clear of vertical structures.
- No flight over houses / buildings.
- No powerlines.
- No trees adjacent to the site.
- Undulating slope in the area as the site sits on a knoll.
- Low grassy vegetation and natural rock.
- No support vehicle access, not accessible by road.
- One helicopter only.
- If fuel or oil spill, damage to alpine vegetation may occur.
- No stock, wildlife or waterfowl likely to be present.
- Members of public present is possible as the site is adjacent to walking tracks. Management of public may be required during holiday periods (small number of hikers only).
- No lighting.
